# Tailwind-First Styling — Mandatory

Style UI with **Tailwind utility classes** first. Custom CSS in `globals.css` or standalone stylesheets is **not allowed** for component-level layout, spacing, color, typography, or shadows unless an exception below applies.

## Default approach

1. **Component markup** — `className={cn("...", className)}` with Tailwind utilities and design tokens (`text-muted-foreground`, `bg-[var(--glass-fill)]`, `rounded-[1.25rem]`, etc.).
2. **shadcn/ui & third-party wrappers** — override via `className` and `*Options.classNames` (e.g. Sonner `toastOptions.classNames`), **not** `unstyled: true` + bespoke CSS blocks.
3. **Shared tokens** — reuse helpers from `config/` (`GLASS_SURFACE`, `STACK_GAP`, `RADIUS_DEEP`) instead of duplicating long class strings.
4. **`cn()`** — merge conditional classes; extract repeated strings to `const` in the same file when a class list is reused.

## Allowed custom CSS (exceptions only)

- **Global design tokens** — `:root` / `.dark` CSS variables in `globals.css`
- **Cross-cutting utilities** already in `@layer components` / `@layer utilities` (e.g. `.glass-backdrop`, sidebar shell) when Tailwind alone cannot express dynamic appearance settings
- **`@keyframes`** only when no equivalent Tailwind/`tw-animate` utility exists — prefer `animate-spin`, `animate-in`, etc. first

## Do not

- Add new `.feature-name { ... }` blocks in `globals.css` for a single component or page
- Use `unstyled: true` on Sonner (or similar) solely to avoid fighting default styles — override with Tailwind instead
- Inline `<style>` tags or CSS modules for CMS admin UI unless explicitly requested

## Examples

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — bespoke globals.css + unstyled
toastOptions={{ unstyled: true, classNames: { toast: "macos-toast" } }}

// ✅ GOOD — shadcn/Sonner pattern with Tailwind
<Sonner
  className="toaster group z-[9999]"
  toastOptions={{
    classNames: {
      toast: cn("group toast rounded-[1.25rem] p-3.5", GLASS_BACKDROP, GLASS_FILL),
      title: "text-sm font-semibold text-foreground",
      description: "text-sm text-muted-foreground",
    },
  }}
/>
```

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — new globals.css block for one panel
// .my-panel { display: flex; gap: 0.75rem; ... }

// ✅ GOOD
<div className="flex gap-3 rounded-xl border border-border p-4">...</div>
```
